  %h3
    Crowd funding site
  %p
    On the Travis CI crowd funding site there is a "Thank you, sponsors" section.
  %p
    Similar to what is layed out on the current staging app we will display 1
    platinum, 2 gold and 4 silver sponsors at once, giving each package a
    different amount of space (although we might want to opt for an even
    smaller amount of space for silver sponsors and instead display more of
    them here).
  %p
    The order of sponsors displayed on page load will be randomized so that
    each sponsor gets an equal chance of being displayed on page load.
  %p
    The whole sponsors list will be paginated (as currently the "Thank you,
    folks" and "What people say" lists are paginated), so curious users have an
    opportunity to flip through the pages.
  %p
    After 5 seconds the next page will be activated automatically (so there
    will be a classical "banner rotation", but in a visually appealing way).


  %h3
    Application sidebar
  %p
    The sidebar will be re-designed so that we have two spots where sponsors
    appear but use less space in total.

  %ul
    %li
      There will be a slot at the top of the sidebar (above the workers list)
      that displays either 1 Platinum or 2 Gold sponsors at a time.
    %li
      There will be another list of sponsors (below the queues lists) that
      displays 8 Silver sponsors at a time as text links.
  %p
    There will be a link to the main Travis CI sponsors page
    %sup
      %a{href: '#fn-3'} 3


  %h3
    Build notification emails
  %p
    We will display 1 Platinum sponsor or 2 Gold sponsors below every build
    notification email. These will be randomized and Platinum sponsors will
    have a 2:1 chance to appear over Gold sponsors.
  %p
    There will be a link to the main Travis CI sponsors page
    %sup
      %a{href: '#fn-3'} 3    


  %h3
    Sponsors page
  %p
    We will add a static page that displays all of our sponsors at once so that
    curious users can review and link to them.
  %p
    This page will be published on http://sponsors.travis-ci.org and simply
    list sponsors in the order of their package size (Platinum, Gold, Silver)
    and in the order of their package booking dates.
  %p
    Each listing will also link to the respective blog post on the Travis CI
    blog as well as other places the sponsor likes to link.


  %h3
    Blog
  %p
    Platinum and Gold sponsors may provide blog posts presenting their company,
    involvement in the open source community and reasons to sponsor Travis CI.
    These blog posts will be published without any editing as dedicated single
    posts as soon as possible once they are available.
  %p
    Silver sponsors may provide contents to summary posts consisiting of 3-5
    parts.  These contents may be up to about X words long (to be specified)
    and will be used to compose summary blog posts as soon as possible once a
    sufficient number of contents from sponsors is available.


  %h3
    Twitter
  %p
    We will tweet about the sponsorship from our Travis CI account as soon
    as all required materials are published in all relevant places (especially
    the listing on the sponsors page).
  %p
    We will also retweet these tweets from at least one of our personal Twitter
    accounts @joshkalderimis, @konstantinhaase and @svenfuchs for Platinum and
    Gold sponsors by default and Silver sponsors on special occasions.


  %h3
    Conference Talks
  %p
    We will show our sponsors' logos on slides and read out names at each
    conference talk we do at conferences on topics related to Travis CI. We
    will need to fit this to the actual presentation but we will do our best to
    draw as much attention to our sponsors as possible.


  %h3
    Office visits and personal stuff
  %p
    The Platinum and Gold packages include options to have Josh and/or Sven
    visit the sponsor's office and meet their team for pair programming
    sessions or other kinds of events. Sponsors can use these office visits to
    direct attention to your company, homepage, service, blog etc.
  %p
    We will retweet sponsor's tweets about these events and will generally try
    our best in order to drive positive attention to our sponsors.


  %h3
    Sticker/swag mailing
  %p
    We will send out one or many stickers to every donor through snail mail.
  %p
    Platinum and Gold sponsors can contribute own stickers or other swag that
    we will include to these mailings. For items that contribute significant
    size the sponsor might need to help with additional postal charges.

